<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>NYT &gt; Technology</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/section/technology</link><description>Technology industry news, commentary, and analysis, with reporting on big tech, startups, and internet culture. The New York Times is a hub for conversation about news and ideas.</description><atom:link rel="self" href="https://rss.nytimes.com/services/xml/rss/nyt/Technology.xml" type="application/rss+xml" /><item><title>The New York Times Amends Lawsuit Against OpenAI and Microsoft</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/25/technology/times-lawsuit-openai-microsoft.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/25/technology/times-lawsuit-openai-microsoft.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/25/technology/times-lawsuit-openai-microsoft.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>In a new court filing, The Times accused Microsoft of encouraging OpenAI to train its A.I. systems using copyrighted articles.</description><dc:creator>Cade Metz</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jun 2026 21:15:28 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">The New York Times</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Copyrights</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Lawsuits</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">journalism</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">journalist</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">news media</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/