amespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Price</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">iPhone</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Laptop</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Electronics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Apple</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Amazon</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Facebook</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Service Content</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/05/business/03techfix/03techfix-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Sisi Yu</media:credit></media:content></item><item><title>Larry Sanger, a Wikipedia Founder, Is Barred From Editing on the Site</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/25/business/media/wikipedia-larry-sanger-barred.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/25/business/media/wikipedia-larry-sanger-barred.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/25/business/media/wikipedia-larry-sanger-barred.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>A vote to bar Larry Sanger indefinitely from the volunteer community of Wikipedia came days after he submitted a proposal on “intellectual diversity.”</description><dc:creator>Adeel Hassan</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jun 2026 11:48:07 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Larry Sanger</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Wikipedia</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-eafs</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/24/multimedia/24xp-wikipedia/24xp-wikipedia-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Ulli Winkler/ullstein bild, via Getty Images</media:credit><media:description>Larry Sanger said that Wikipedia was “one of the most effective organs of establishment propaganda in history.”</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Om Malik, Whose Blog Shaped How Silicon Valley Saw Itself, Dies at 59</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/26/technology/om-malik-dead.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/26/technology/om-malik-dead.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/26/technology/om-malik-dead.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Gigaom, which he started in 2001, established him as a leading voice in the tech world and signaled a shift in how the media covered the industry.</description><dc:creator>Clay Risen</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 26 Jun 2026 22:41:23 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Om Malik</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Obituary</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Blog</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">journalism</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">journalist</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">news media</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">GigaOm</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/26/multimedia/00Malik--zljw/00Malik--zljw-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Peter DaSilva for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Om Malik in 2012. His blog, Gigaom, covered Silicon Valley with a mixture of hot scoops and sharp opinions.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>U.S. Loosens Restrictions on Anthropic’s Mythos A.I. Model</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/26/technology/anthropic-mythos-government-restrictions.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/26/technology/anthropic-mythos-government-restrictions.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/26/technology/anthropic-mythos-government-restrictions.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The move de-escalates a clash between the Trump administration and the company over its cutting-edge artificial intelligence systems.</description><dc:creator>Sheera Frenkel</dc:creator><pubDate>Sat, 27 Jun 2026 00:21:36 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Commerce Department</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US Politics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Donald Trump</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/26/business/26biz-anthropic-deal-mythos/26biz-anthropic-deal-mythos-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Gabby Jones/Bloomberg</media:credit><media:description>In a letter on Friday, the Commerce Department gave Anthropic permission to restore some clients’ access to one of its most powerful artificial intelligence models, Mythos 5.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Should You Outsource Your Morning Routine to a Chatbot?</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/04/magazine/ai-chatbot-morning-routine-videos.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/04/magazine/ai-chatbot-morning-routine-videos.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/04/magazine/ai-chatbot-morning-routine-videos.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>A.I. wants to help you start the day. Its suggestions? Drink coffee and get dressed.</description><dc:creator>Sophie Haigney</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2026 09:03:39 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Habits and Routines</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Social Media</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">TikTok</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/14/magazine/14mag-screenland/14mag-screenland-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Aniyah Uniquee/@Aniyahuniquee</media:credit></media:content></item></channel></rss>